AcceptInput.detail: CBaseEntity.AcceptInput(input: string, param: string, activator: handle, caller: handle) -> bool
AcceptInput.desc: Generate a synchronous I/O event. Unlike `EntFireByHandle`, this is processed immediately. Returns false if `input` is a null/empty string, or if the input wasn't handled.

AddEFlags.desc:
Adds the supplied `flags` to the **Entity Flags** in the entity. *(m_iEFlags datamap)*

See [FEntityEFlags](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FEntityEFlags).

AddFlag.desc:
Adds the supplied `flags` to another separate player-related entity flags system in the entity. *(m_fFlags datamap)*

See [FPlayer](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FPlayer).

AddSolidFlags.desc:
Adds the supplied `flags` to the *Solid Flags* in the entity. *(m_Collision.m_usSolidFlags datamap)*

See [FSolid](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FSolid).

ApplyAbsVelocityImpulse.desc: Apply a Velocity Impulse as a world space impulse vector. Works for most physics-based objects including dropped weapons and even dropped Sandviches.

ApplyLocalAngularVelocityImpulse.desc: Apply an Angular Velocity Impulse in entity local space. The direction of the input vector is the rotation axis, and the length is the magnitude of the impulse.

BecomeRagdollOnClient.desc: Acts like the `BecomeRagdoll` input, with the required `impulse` value applied as a force on the ragdoll. Does NOT spawn a `[prop_ragdoll](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/prop_ragdoll)` or any other entity.

ClearFlags.desc: Sets the player-related entity flags to 0 on an entity, clearing them.

ClearSolidFlags.desc: Sets *Solid Flags* to 0 on an entity, clearing them.

ConnectOutput.desc: Adds an I/O connection that will call the named function when the specified output fires.

DisableDraw.desc: Disable drawing and transmitting the entity to clients. *(adds EF_NODRAW)*

DisconnectOutput.desc: Removes a connected script function from an I/O event.

DispatchSpawn.desc: Alternative dispatch spawn, same as the one in CEntities, for convenience.

EmitSound.desc: Plays a sound from this entity. The sound must be precached first for it to play (using `PrecacheSound` or `PrecacheScriptSound`).

EnableDraw.desc: Enable drawing and transmitting the entity to clients. *(removes EF_NODRAW)*

EyeAngles.desc: Returns the entity's eye angles. Acts like `GetAbsAngles` if the entity does not support it.

EyePosition.desc: Get vector to eye position - absolute coords. Acts like `GetOrigin` if the entity does not support it.

FirstMoveChild.desc: Returns the most-recent entity parented to this one.

GetAbsAngles.desc: Get the entity's pitch, yaw, and roll as **QAngles**.

GetAbsVelocity.desc: Returns the current absolute velocity of the entity.

GetAngularVelocity.desc: Get the local angular velocity - returns a **Vector** of pitch, yaw, and roll.

GetBaseVelocity.desc: Returns any constant velocity currently being imparted onto the entity. This includes being pushed by effects like

GetBoundingMaxs.desc: Get a vector containing max bounds, centered on object.

GetBoundingMaxsOriented.desc: Get a vector containing max bounds, centered on object, taking the object's orientation into account.

GetBoundingMins.desc: Get a vector containing min bounds, centered on object.

GetBoundingMinsOriented.desc: Get a vector containing min bounds, centered on object, taking the object's orientation into account.

GetCenter.desc: Gets center point of the entity in world coordinates / Get center origin of area.

GetCollisionGroup.desc: Gets the current collision group of the entity.

GetEntityHandle.desc: Get the entity as an EHANDLE.

GetForwardVector.desc: Get the forward vector of the entity.

GetFriction.desc: Get PLAYER friction, ignored for objects.

GetModelKeyValues.desc: Get a KeyValue class instance on this entity's model.

GetModelName.desc: Returns the name of the model.

GetMoveParent.desc: If in hierarchy, retrieves the entity's parent.

GetName.desc: Get entity's targetname/Gets the weapon's internal name.

GetOrigin.desc: This is `GetAbsOrigin` with a funny script name for some reason. Not changing it for legacy compat though.

GetPreTemplateName.desc: Get the entity name stripped of template unique decoration.

GetRightVector.desc: Get the right vector of the entity.

GetRootMoveParent.desc: If in hierarchy, walks up the hierarchy to find the root parent.

GetScriptId.desc: Retrieve the unique identifier used to refer to the entity within the scripting system.

GetScriptScope.desc: Retrieve the script-side data associated with an entity.

GetScriptThinkFunc.desc: Retrieve the name of the current script think func.

GetSoundDuration.desc: Returns float duration of the sound. Actor model name is optional and can be left null.

GetUpVector.desc: Get the up vector of the entity.

GetWaterLevel.desc: This function tells you how much of the entity is underwater. It returns a value of 0 if not underwater, 1 if the feet are (touching water brush), 2 if the waist is (center of the hull of the entity), and 3 if the head is (eyes position).

GetWaterType.desc: It returns the type of water the entity is currently submerged in. 32 for water and 16 for slime.

IsPlayer.desc: Checks whether the entity is a player or not.

IsValid.desc: Checks whether the entity still exists. Useful when storing entity handles and needing to check if the entity was not deleted.

Kill.desc: Removes the entity. Equivalent of firing the `Kill` I/O input, but instantaneous.

LocalEyeAngles.desc: Returns the entity's local eye angles.

NextMovePeer.desc: Returns the next entity parented *with* the entity. Intended for iteration use with `FirstMoveChild()`.

PrecacheModel.desc: Precache a model (`.mdl`) or sprite (`.vmt`). The extension must be specified.

PrecacheScriptSound.desc: Precache a sound script. Same as `PrecacheSoundScript`.

PrecacheSoundScript.desc: Precache a sound script. Same as `PrecacheScriptSound`.

SetAbsAngles.desc: Set entity pitch, yaw, roll as QAngles. Does not work on players, use `SnapEyeAngles` instead.

SetAbsVelocity.desc: Sets the current absolute velocity of the entity. Does nothing on [VPhysics](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/VPhysics) objects (such as `prop_physics`). For those, use `SetPhysVelocity` instead.

SetAbsOrigin.desc: Sets the absolute origin of the entity.

SetAngularVelocity.detail: CBaseEntity.SetAngularVelocity(pitch: float, yaw: float, roll: float) -> null

SetCollisionGroup.desc:
Set the current collision group of the entity.

See [ECollisionGroup](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ECollisionGroup).

SetDrawEnabled.desc: Enables drawing if you pass true, disables drawing if you pass false.

SetForwardVector.desc: Set the orientation of the entity to have this forward vector.

SetGravity.desc: Sets a multiplier for gravity. 1 is default gravity.

SetMaxHealth.desc: Sets the maximum health this entity can have. Does not update the current health, so `SetHealth` should be used afterwards.

SetModel.desc: Set a model for this entity.

SetSize.desc: Sets the bounding box's scale for this entity.

SetWaterLevel.desc: This sets how much of the entity is underwater. Setting it to 0 means it is not underwater, 1 if the feet are (touching water brush), 2 if the waist is (center of the hull of the entity), and 3 if the head is (eyes position).

SetWaterType.desc: Set the type of water the entity is currently submerged in. Generic values to use are 32 for water and 16 for slime.

StopSound.desc: Stops a sound on this entity.

TakeDamage.detail: CBaseEntity.TakeDamage(damage: float, damage_type: FDmgType, attacker: handle) -> null
TakeDamage.desc:
Deals damage to the entity.

See [FDmgType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FDmgType).

TakeDamageEx.detail: CBaseEntity.TakeDamageEx(inflictor: handle, attacker: handle, weapon: handle, damage_force: Vector, damage_position: Vector, damage: float, damage_type: FDmgType) -> null

TakeDamageCustom.detail: CBaseEntity.TakeDamageCustom(inflictor: handle, attacker: handle, weapon: handle, damage_force: Vector, damage_position: Vector, damage: float, damage_type: FDmgType, custom_damage_type: ETFDmgCustom) -> null
TakeDamageCustom.desc:
Extended version of `TakeDamageEx` that can apply a custom damage type.

See [FDmgType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FDmgType) ,[ETFDmgCustom](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFDmgCustom).

Teleport.detail: CBaseEntity.Teleport(use_origin: bool, origin: Vector, use_angles: bool, angles: QAngle, use_velocity: bool, velocity: Vector) -> null
Teleport.desc: Teleports this entity. For this function, set the bools to false if you want that entity's property unchanged. (do not use null arguments!)

TerminateScriptScope.desc: Clear the current script scope for this entity.

ValidateScriptScope.desc: Create a script scope for an entity if it doesn't already exist. The return value is always true, unless the script VM is disabled in launch options.

DispatchAnimEvents.desc: Dispatch animation events to a CBaseAnimating entity.

FindBodygroupByName.desc: Find a bodygroup ID by name. Returns -1 if the bodygroup does not exist.

GetAttachmentAngles.desc: Get an attachment's angles as a QAngle, by ID.

GetAttachmentBone.desc: Get an attachment's parent bone index by ID.

GetAttachmentOrigin.desc: Get an attachment's origin as a Vector, by ID.

GetBodygroup.desc: Get the bodygroup value by bodygroup ID.

GetBodygroupName.desc: Get the bodygroup's name by ID.

GetBodygroupPartName.desc: Get the bodygroup's name by group and part.

GetBoneAngles.desc: Get the bone's angles as a QAngle, by ID.

GetBoneOrigin.desc: Get the bone's origin Vector by ID.

GetCycle.desc: Gets the model's current animation cycle rate. Ranges from 0.0 to 1.0.

GetPlaybackRate.desc: Get the current animation's playback rate.

GetSequenceActivityName.desc: Get the activity name for a sequence by sequence ID.

GetSequenceDuration.desc: Get a sequence duration in seconds by sequence ID.

GetSequenceName.desc: Get a sequence name by sequence ID. Returns "Not Found!" if ID is -1, "Unknown" if the sequence doesn't exist or "No model!" if no model is assigned.

IsSequenceFinished.desc: Ask whether the main sequence is done playing.

LookupActivity.desc: Get the named activity index. Returns -1 if the activity does not exist.

LookupAttachment.desc: Get the named attachment index. Returns 0 if the attachment does not exist.

LookupBone.desc: Get the named bone index. Returns -1 if the bone does not exist.

LookupPoseParameter.desc: Gets the pose parameter's index. Returns -1 if the pose parameter does not exist.

LookupSequence.desc: Looks up a sequence by names of sequences or activities. Returns -1 if the sequence does not exist.

ResetSequence.desc: Reset a sequence by sequence ID. If the ID is different than the current sequence, switch to the new sequence.

SetCycle.desc: Sets the model's current animation cycle from 0 to 1.

SetModelSimple.desc: Set a model for this entity. Matches easier behaviour of the SetModel input, automatically precaches, maintains sequence/cycle if possible. Also clears the bone cache.

SetModelScale.desc: Changes a model's scale over time. Set the change duration to 0.0 to change the scale instantly.

SetPlaybackRate.desc: Set the current animation's playback rate.

SetPoseParameter.desc: Sets a pose parameter value. Returns the effective value after clamping or looping.

SetSequence.desc: Plays a sequence by sequence ID.

StopAnimation.desc: Stop the current animation (same as SetPlaybackRate 0.0).

StudioFrameAdvance.desc: Advance animation frame to some time in the future with an automatically calculated interval.

StudioFrameAdvanceManual.desc: Advance animation frame to some time in the future with a manual interval.

GetPrimaryAmmoCount.desc: Current primary ammo count if no clip is used or to give a player if they pick up this weapon legacy style (not TF).

GetSecondaryAmmoCount.desc: Current secondary ammo count if no clip is used or to give a player if they pick up this weapon legacy style (not TF).

HasPrimaryAmmo.desc: Do we have any primary ammo?

HasSecondaryAmmo.desc: Do we have any secondary ammo?

IsAllowedToSwitch.desc: Are we allowed to switch to this weapon?

IsMeleeWeapon.desc: Returns whether this is a melee weapon.

SetCustomViewModel.desc: Sets a custom view model for this weapon by model name.

SetCustomViewModelModelIndex.desc: Sets a custom view model for this weapon by modelindex.

UsesClipsForAmmo1.desc: Do we use clips for ammo 1?

UsesClipsForAmmo2.desc: Do we use clips for ammo 2?

VisibleInWeaponSelection.desc: Is this weapon visible in weapon selection?

PlayScene.desc: Play the specified .vcd file, causing the related characters to speak and subtitles to play.

GetLastKnownArea.desc: Return the last nav area occupied, NULL if unknown.

GetForceLocalDraw.desc: Whether the player is being forced by SetForceLocalDraw to be drawn.

GetPlayerMaxs.desc: Get a vector containing max bounds of the player in local space. The player's model scale will affect the result.

GetPlayerMins.desc: Get a vector containing min bounds of the player in local space. The player's model scale will affect the result.

GetScriptOverlayMaterial.desc: Gets the current overlay material set by SetScriptOverlayMaterial.

IsNoclipping.desc: Returns true if the player is in noclip mode.

SetForceLocalDraw.desc: Forces the player to be drawn as if they were in thirdperson.

SetScriptOverlayMaterial.desc: Sets the overlay material that can't be overriden by other overlays. E.g. Jarate.

SnapEyeAngles.desc: Snap the player's eye angles to this.

ViewPunchReset.desc: Reset's the player's view punch if the offset stays below the given tolerance.

AddAttribute.detail: CEconEntity.AddAttribute(attribute: string, value: float, duration: float) -> null
AddAttribute.desc: Add an attribute to the entity. <s>Set duration to 0 or lower for the attribute to be applied forever</s> See the bug below. The attribute must be one that exists in the game, invalid ones will not be added.

GetAttribute.desc: Get an attribute float from the entity. If the attribute does not exist, returns `default_value`.

RemoveAttribute.desc: Remove an attribute from the entity.

ReapplyProvision.desc: Relinks attributes to provisioners, e.g. calling this on a weapon will add it's attributes to the player.

AddCondEx.detail: CTFPlayer.AddCondEx(cond: ETFCond, duration: float, provider: handle) -> null

AddCurrency.desc: Kaching! Give the player some cash for game modes with upgrades, ie. MvM. The new value is bounded between 0-30000.

AddCustomAttribute.detail: CTFPlayer.AddCustomAttribute(attribute: string, value: float, duration: float) -> null
AddCustomAttribute.desc: Add a custom attribute to the player. Set duration to 0 or lower for the attribute to be applied forever. The attribute must be one that exists in the game, invalid ones will not be added.

ApplyPunchImpulseX.desc: Apply a view punch along the pitch angle. Used to flinch players when hit. If the player is a fully charged scoped-in sniper and the weapon has the `aiming_no_flinch` attribute, the punch will not apply. Returns true if the punch was applied.

BleedPlayer.desc: Make a player bleed for a set duration of time.

BleedPlayerEx.detail: CTFPlayer.BleedPlayerEx(duration: float, damage: int, endless: bool, custom_damage_type: ETFDmgCustom) -> null
BleedPlayerEx.desc:
Make a player bleed for a set duration of time, or forever, with specific damage per tick and damage_custom index.

See [ETFDmgCustom](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFDmgCustom).

CanAirDash.desc: Can the player air dash/double jump?

CanGetWet.desc: Can the player get wet by jarate/milk?

CanJump.desc: Can the player jump? Returns false if the player is taunting or if the `no_jump` attribute is present and non-zero. There is other conditions that prevent jumping but this function by itself doesn't check those.

ClearTauntAttack.desc: Stops active taunt from damaging or cancels Rock-Paper-Scissors result.

DoTauntAttack.desc: Performs taunts attacks if available. Player must be already taunting and taunt must have a valid attack assigned (`taunt attack name` attribute).

DropFlag.desc: Force player to drop the flag (intelligence).

DropRune.desc:
Force player to drop the rune.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

EndLongTaunt.desc: Stops a looping taunt (obeys minimum time rules and plays outro animation if available).

EquipWearableViewModel.desc: Equips a wearable on the viewmodel. Intended to be used with [tf_wearable_vm](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/tf_wearable_vm) entities.

FiringTalk.desc: Makes eg. a heavy go AAAAAAAAAAaAaa like they are firing their minigun.

ForceChangeTeam.desc:
Force player to change their team. Setting the bool to true will not remove nemesis relationships or reset the player's class, as well as not slaying the player.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

ForceRegenerateAndRespawn.desc: Force regenerates and respawns the player.

GetClassEyeHeight.desc: Gets the eye height of the player.

GetCondDuration.desc:
Returns duration of the condition. Returns 0 if the cond is not applied. Returns -1 if the cond is infinite.

See [ETFCond](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFCond).

GetCustomAttribute.desc: Get an attribute float from the player. If the attribute does not exist, returns `default_value`.

GetCurrency.desc: Get player's cash for game modes with upgrades, ie. MvM.

GetGrapplingHookTarget.desc: What entity is the player grappling?

GetTauntAttackTime.desc: Timestamp until a taunt attack "lasts". 0 if unavailable.

GetTimeSinceCalledForMedic.desc: When did the player last call medic.

HasItem.desc: Currently holding an item? Eg. capture flag.

HandleTauntCommand.desc: Spoofs a taunt command from the player, as if they selected this taunt. This can be abused to give the player any taunt, see the [examples page](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/VScript_Examples#Giving a taunt).

IgnitePlayer.desc: Supposed to set the player on fire, but...

IsAllowedToRemoveTaunt.desc: Returns true if the taunt will be stopped.

IsBotOfType.desc:
Returns true if the player matches this bot type. Only one type of bot exists which is reserved for AI bots (not [https://wiki.teamfortress.com/wiki/Bots#Puppet_bots puppet bots]). 0 is used for real players or puppet bots. Use `IsFakeClient` to check for a puppet bot instead.

See [EBotType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#EBotType).

IsCallingForMedic.desc: Is this player calling for medic?

IsFakeClient.desc: Returns true if the player is a puppet or AI bot. To check if the player is a AI bot (`CTFBot`) specifically, use `IsBotOfType` instead.

IsMiniBoss.desc: Is this player an MvM mini-boss?

IsPlacingSapper.desc: Returns true if we placed a sapper in the last few moments.

IsSapping.desc: Returns true if we are currently sapping.

Regenerate.desc: Resupplies a player. If refill health/ammo is set, clears negative conds, gives back player health/ammo.

RemoveAllObjects.desc: Remove all player objects. Eg. dispensers/sentries.

RemoveCond.desc:
Removes a condition. Does not remove a condition if the minimum duration has not passed. Does nothing if the condition isn't added (interally does `InCond` check).

See [ETFCond](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFCond).

RemoveCondEx.desc:
Extended version of above function. Allows forcefully removing the condition even if minimum duration is not met.

See [ETFCond](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFCond).

RemoveCurrency.desc: Take away money from a player for reasons such as ie. spending. Lower bounded to 0.

RemoveCustomAttribute.desc: Remove a custom attribute to the player.

SetCurrency.desc: Set player's cash for game modes with upgrades, ie. MvM. Does not have any bounds checking.

SetCustomModel.desc: Sets a custom player model without animations (model will T-pose). To enable animations, use `SetCustomModelWithClassAnimations` instead.

SetCustomModelWithClassAnimations.desc: Sets a custom player model with full animations.

SetGrapplingHookTarget.desc: Set the player's target grapple entity.

SetHudHideFlags.desc:
Force hud hide flags to a value.

See [FHideHUD](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FHideHUD).

SetIsMiniBoss.desc: Make this player an MvM mini-boss.

SetPlayerClass.desc:
Sets the player class. Updates the player's visuals and model.

See [ETFClass](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFClass).

SetRPSResult.desc: Rig the result of Rock-Paper-Scissors (0 - rock, 1 - paper, 2 - scissors).

SetVehicleReverseTime.desc: Set the timestamp when kart was reversed.

StopTaunt.desc: Stops current taunt. If `remove_prop` is true, the taunt prop will be immediately deleted instead of potentially delaying.

StunPlayer.detail: CTFPlayer.StunPlayer(duration: float, move_speed_reduction: float, flags: TF_STUN, attacker: handle) -> null
StunPlayer.desc:
Stuns the player for a specified duration. Move speed reduction is a fraction (0 = no reduction. 1 = total reduction, no movement). Flag combinations control the stun type and behavior.

See [TF_STUN](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#TF_STUN).

Taunt.desc:
Performs a taunt if allowed. Concept is the "voiceline" index to use with the taunt. For `TAUNT_SHOW_ITEM` and `TAUNT_BASE_WEAPON` this is set automatically. `TAUNT_LONG` is not supported.

See [FTaunts](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTaunts) ,[MP_CONCEPT](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#MP_CONCEPT).

TryToPickupBuilding.desc: Make the player attempt to pick up a building in front of them.

Weapon_DropEx.detail: CTFPlayer.Weapon_DropEx(weapon: handle, target: Vector, velocity: Vector) -> null

Weapon_Equip.desc: Equips a weapon in the player. This places it inside the `m_hMyWeapons` array.

Weapon_Switch.desc: Attempts a switch to the given weapon, if present in the player's inventory (`m_hMyWeapons` array).

AddBotAttribute.desc:
Sets attribute flags on this TFBot.

See [FTFBotAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTFBotAttributeType).

ClearAllBotAttributes.desc: Clears all attribute flags on this TFBot.

ClearBehaviorFlag.desc:
Clear the given behavior flag(s) for this bot.

See [TFBOT_BEHAVIOR](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#TFBOT_BEHAVIOR).

DelayedThreatNotice.desc: Notice the threat after a delay in seconds.

DisbandCurrentSquad.desc: Forces the current squad to be entirely disbanded by everyone.

FindVantagePoint.desc: Get the nav area of the closest vantage point (within distance).

GetActionPoint.desc: Get the given action point for this bot.

GetAllBotTags.desc: Get all bot tags. The key is the index, and the value is the tag.

GetHomeArea.desc: Sets the home nav area of the bot.

GetDifficulty.desc: Returns the bot's difficulty level. See [Constants.ETFBotDifficultyType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotDifficultyType).

GetMaxVisionRangeOverride.desc: Gets the max vision range override for the bot

GetMission.desc: Get this bot's current mission. See [ETFBotMissionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotMissionType).

GetMissionTarget.desc: Get this bot's current mission target.

GetNearestKnownSappableTarget.desc: Gets the nearest known sappable target.

GetPrevMission.desc: Get this bot's previous mission. See [ETFBotMissionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotMissionType).

GetSpawnArea.desc: Return the nav area of where we spawned.

HasBotAttribute.desc:
Checks if this TFBot has the given attributes.

See [FTFBotAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTFBotAttributeType).

HasBotTag.desc: Checks if this TFBot has the given bot tag.

HasMission.desc:
Return true if the given mission is this bot's current mission.

See [ETFBotMissionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotMissionType).

HasWeaponRestriction.desc:
Checks if this TFBot has the given weapon restriction flags.

See [TFBotWeaponRestrictionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#TFBotWeaponRestrictionType).

IsAttentionFocused.desc: Is our attention focused right now?

IsAttentionFocusedOn.desc: Is our attention focused on this entity.

IsBehaviorFlagSet.desc:
Return true if the given behavior flag(s) are set for this bot.

See [TFBOT_BEHAVIOR](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#TFBOT_BEHAVIOR).

IsDifficulty.desc:
Returns true/false if the bot's difficulty level matches.

See [ETFBotDifficultyType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotDifficultyType).

IsInASquad.desc: Checks if we are in a squad.

IsOnAnyMission.desc: Return true if this bot has a current mission.

IsWeaponRestricted.desc: Checks if the given weapon is restricted for use on the bot.

LeaveSquad.desc: Makes us leave the current squad (if any).

RemoveBotAttribute.desc:
Removes attribute flags on this TFBot.

See [FTFBotAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTFBotAttributeType).

SetActionPoint.desc: Set the given action point for this bot.

SetAttentionFocus.desc: Sets our current attention focus to this entity.

SetAutoJump.desc: Sets if the bot should automatically jump, and how often.

SetBehaviorFlag.desc:
Set the given behavior flag(s) for this bot.

See [TFBOT_BEHAVIOR](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#TFBOT_BEHAVIOR).

SetDifficulty.desc:
Sets the bots difficulty level.

See [ETFBotDifficultyType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotDifficultyType).

SetHomeArea.desc: Set the home nav area of the bot, may be null.

SetMaxVisionRangeOverride.desc: Sets max vision range override for the bot.

SetMission.desc:
Set this bot's current mission to the given mission.

See [ETFBotMissionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotMissionType).

SetMissionTarget.desc: Set this bot's mission target to the given entity.

SetPrevMission.desc:
Set this bot's previous mission to the given mission.

See [ETFBotMissionType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFBotMissionType).

SetScaleOverride.desc: Sets the scale override for the bot.

SetShouldQuickBuild.desc: Sets if the bot should build instantly.

ShouldAutoJump.desc: Returns if the bot should automatically jump.

ShouldQuickBuild.desc: Returns if the bot should build instantly.

SetResolvePlayerCollisions.desc: Sets whether the entity should push away players intersecting its bounding box. On by default.

AddIncomingConnection.desc:
Add areas that connect TO this area by a ONE-WAY link.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

ClearAttributeTF.desc:
Clear TF-specific area attribute bits.

See [FTFNavAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTFNavAttributeType).

ComputeClosestPointInPortal.detail: CTFNavArea.ComputeClosestPointInPortal(to: handle, dir: ENavDirType, close_pos: Vector) -> Vector
ComputeClosestPointInPortal.desc:
Compute closest point within the "portal" between to an area's direction from the given position.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

ComputeDirection.desc: Return direction from this area to the given point.

ConnectTo.desc:
Connect this area to given area in given direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

Contains.desc: Return true if other area is on or above this area, but no others.

ContainsOrigin.desc: Return true if given point is on or above this area, but no others.

DebugDrawFilled.detail: CTFNavArea.DebugDrawFilled(r: int, g: int, b: int, a: int, duration: float, no_depth_test: bool, margin: float) -> null
DebugDrawFilled.desc: Draw area as a filled rectangle of the given color.

Disconnect.desc: Disconnect this area from given area.

FindRandomSpot.desc: Get random origin within extent of area.

GetAdjacentArea.desc:
Return the n'th adjacent area in the given direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetAdjacentAreas.desc:
Fills a passed in table with all adjacent areas in the given direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetAdjacentCount.desc:
Get the number of adjacent areas in the given direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetAvoidanceObstacleHeight.desc: Returns the maximum height of the obstruction above the ground.

GetCorner.desc:
Get corner origin of area.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetDistanceSquaredToPoint.desc: Return shortest distance between point and this area.

GetDoor.desc: Returns the door entity above the area.

GetElevator.desc: Returns the elevator if in an elevator's path.

GetElevatorAreas.desc: Fills table with a collection of areas reachable via elevator from this area.

GetIncomingConnections.desc:
Fills a passed in table with areas connected TO this area by a ONE-WAY link (ie: we have no connection back to them).

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetParent.desc: Returns the area just prior to this one in the search path.

GetParentHow.desc: Returns how we get from parent to us.

GetPlaceName.desc: Get place name if it exists, null otherwise.

GetPlayerCount.desc:
Return number of players of given team currently within this area (team of zero means any/all).

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

GetRandomAdjacentArea.desc:
Return a random adjacent area in the given direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

GetSizeX.desc: Return the area size along the X axis.

GetSizeY.desc: Return the area size along the Y axis.

GetTravelDistanceToBombTarget.desc: Gets the travel distance to the MvM bomb target.

GetZ.desc: Return Z of area at (x,y) of `pos`.

HasAttributeTF.desc:
Has TF-specific area attribute bits of the given ones.

See [FTFNavAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FTFNavAttributeType).

HasAttributes.desc:
Has area attribute bits of the given ones?.

See [FNavAttributeType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FNavAttributeType).

HasAvoidanceObstacle.desc: Returns true if there's a large, immobile object obstructing this area.

IsBlocked.desc:
Return true if team is blocked in this area.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

IsBottleneck.desc: Returns true if area is a bottleneck. (tiny narrow areas with only one path).

IsCompletelyVisibleToTeam.desc:
Return true if given area is completely visible from somewhere in this area by someone on the team.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

IsConnected.desc:
Return true if this area is connected to other area in given direction. (If you set direction to -1 or 4, it will automatically check all directions for a connection).

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

IsCoplanar.desc: Return true if this area and given. area are approximately co-planar.

IsDamaging.desc: Return true if this area is marked to have continuous damage.

IsDegenerate.desc: Return true if this area is badly formed.

IsEdge.desc:
Return true if there are no bi-directional links on the given side.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

IsFlat.desc: Return true if this area is approximately flat.

IsOverlapping.desc: Return true if `area` overlaps our 2D extents.

IsOverlappingOrigin.desc: Return true if `pos` is within 2D extents of area.

IsPotentiallyVisibleToTeam.desc:
Return true if any portion of this area is visible to anyone on the given team.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

IsReachableByTeam.desc:
Is this area reachable by the given team?

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

IsRoughlySquare.desc: Return true if this area is approximately square.

IsTFMarked.desc: Is this nav area marked with the current marking scope?

IsUnderwater.desc: Return true if area is underwater.

IsValidForWanderingPopulation.desc: Returns true if area is valid for wandering population.

IsVisible.desc: Return true if area is visible from the given eyepoint.

MarkAsBlocked.desc:
Mark this area as blocked for team.

See [ETFTeam](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ETFTeam).

MarkAsDamaging.desc: Mark this area is damaging for the next `duration` seconds.

MarkObstacleToAvoid.desc: Marks the obstructed status of the nav area.

RemoveOrthogonalConnections.desc:
Removes all connections in directions to left and right of specified direction.

See [ENavDirType](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#ENavDirType).

SetPlaceName.desc: Set place name. If you pass null, the place name will be set to nothing.

TFMark.desc: Mark this nav area with the current marking scope.

FindKey.desc: Find a sub key by the key name.

GetFirstSubKey.desc: Return the first sub key object.

GetKeyBool.desc: Return the key value as a bool.

GetKeyFloat.desc: Return the key value as a float.

GetKeyInt.desc: Return the key value as an integer.

GetKeyString.desc: Return the key value as a string.

GetNextKey.desc: Return the next neighbor key object to the one the method is called on.

IsKeyEmpty.desc: Returns true if the named key has no value.

ReleaseKeyValues.desc: Releases the contents of the instance.

SpawnEntity.desc: Create an entity at the location of the maker.

SpawnEntityAtEntityOrigin.desc: Create an entity at the location of a specified entity instance.

SpawnEntityAtLocation.desc: Create an entity at a specified location and orientation, orientation is Euler angle in degrees (pitch, yaw, roll).

SpawnEntityAtNamedEntityOrigin.desc: Create an entity at the location of a named entity. If multiple entities have the same name, only the one with the lowest entity index will be targeted.

GetFuturePosition.desc: Get a position on the track X seconds in the future.

AddTemplate.desc: Add an entity with the given keyvalues to the template spawner, similar to `SpawnEntityFromTable`. The number of templates allowed is unlimited.

SetGroupSpawnTables.desc: Unused. This only stores a reference to the two tables which is removed when the

AddBroadcastTeamTarget.desc: Adds a team (by index) to the broadcast list.

EstimateLength.desc: Returns length of this scene in seconds.

FindNamedEntity.desc: Given an entity reference, such as !target, get actual entity from scene object.

IsPaused.desc: If this scene is currently paused.

IsPlayingBack.desc: If this scene is currently playing.

LoadSceneFromString.desc: Given a dummy scene name and a vcd string, load the scene.

RemoveBroadcastTeamTarget.desc: Removes a team (by index) from the broadcast list.

CCallChainer.detail: CCallChainer(function_prefix: string, scope: table = null) -> CCallChainer
CCallChainer.desc: Creates a CCallChainer object that'll collect functions that have a matching prefix in the given scope.

PostScriptExecute.desc: Search for all non-native functions with matching prefixes, then push them into the `chains` table.

Call.desc: Find an unprefixed function name in the `chains` table and call it with the given arguments.

CSimpleCallChainer.detail: CSimpleCallChainer(prefix: string, scope: table = null, exactMatch: bool = false) -> CSimpleCallChainer
CSimpleCallChainer.desc: Creates a CSimpleCallChainer object that'll collect functions that have a matching prefix in the given scope, unless it seek for an exact name match.

FlagForUpdate.desc: Flag this bot for update (or not to update if `toggle` is false).

GetImmobileDuration.desc: How long have we been immobile.

GetImmobileSpeedThreshold.desc: Return units/second below which this actor is considered immobile.

IsEnemy.desc: Return true if given entity is our enemy.

IsFlaggedForUpdate.desc: Is this bot flagged for update.

IsFriend.desc: Return true if given entity is our friend.

IsImmobile.desc: Return true if we haven't moved in awhile.

Approach.desc: The primary locomotive method. Goal determines the destination position to move towards. goal_weight determines the priority of this path, you can set this to 1.0 generally speaking.

ClearStuckStatus.desc: Reset stuck status to un-stuck. Reason message is shown when debugging nextbots.

ClimbUpToLedge.detail: ILocomotion.ClimbUpToLedge(goal_pos: Vector, goal_forward: Vector, obstacle: handle) -> bool
ClimbUpToLedge.desc: Initiate a jump to an adjacent high ledge, return false if climb can't start.

DriveTo.desc: Move the bot to the precise given position immediately, updating internal state.

FaceTowards.desc: Rotate body to face towards target.

FractionPotentialGap.desc: If the locomotor cannot jump over the gap, returns the fraction of the jumpable ray.

FractionPotentiallyTraversable.detail: ILocomotion.FractionPotentiallyTraversable(from: Vector, to: Vector, immediately: bool) -> float
FractionPotentiallyTraversable.desc: If the locomotor could not move along the line given, returns the fraction of the walkable ray. If `immediately` is true, breakables are considered non-traverseable.

GetDeathDropHeight.desc: Distance at which we will die if we fall.

GetDesiredSpeed.desc: Get desired speed for locomotor movement.

GetFeet.desc: Return position of feet - the driving point where the bot contacts the ground.

GetGround.desc: Return the current ground entity or NULL if not on the ground.

GetGroundMotionVector.desc: Return unit vector in XY plane describing our direction of motion - even if we are currently not moving.

GetGroundNormal.desc: Surface normal of the ground we are in contact with.

GetGroundSpeed.desc: Return current world space speed in XY plane.

GetMaxJumpHeight.desc: Return maximum height of a jump.

GetMotionVector.desc: Return unit vector describing our direction of motion - even if we are currently not moving.

GetSpeed.desc: Return current world space speed (magnitude of velocity).

GetSpeedLimit.desc: Get maximum speed bot can reach, regardless of desired speed.

GetStepHeight.desc: If delta Z is lower than this, we can step up the surface (like a stair step), but if delta Z is greater than this, we have to jump to get up.

GetStuckDuration.desc: Return how long we've been stuck.

GetTraversableSlopeLimit.desc: Return Z component of unit normal of steepest traversable slope.

HasPotentialGap.desc: Checks if there is a possible gap that will need to be jumped over. Returns fraction of ray from 0 to 1.

IsAbleToClimb.desc: Return true if this bot can climb arbitrary geometry it encounters.

IsAbleToJumpAcrossGaps.desc: Return true if this bot can jump across gaps in its path.

IsAreaTraversable.desc: Return true if given area can be used for navigation.

IsAttemptingToMove.desc: Return true if we have tried to Approach() or DriveTo() very recently.

IsClimbingUpToLedge.desc: Is climbing up to a high ledge.

IsEntityTraversable.desc: Return true if the entity handle is traversable. If `immediately` is true, breakables are considered non-traverseable.

IsGap.desc: Return true if there is a gap at this position.

IsJumpingAcrossGap.desc: Is jumping across a gap to the far side.

IsOnGround.desc: Return true if standing on something.

IsPotentiallyTraversable.detail: ILocomotion.IsPotentiallyTraversable(from: Vector, to: Vector, immediately: bool) -> float
IsPotentiallyTraversable.desc: Checks if this locomotor could potentially move along the line given. Returns fraction of trace result (1 = clear). If `immediately` is true, breakables are considered non-traverseable.

IsScrambling.desc: Is in the middle of a complex action (climbing a ladder, climbing a ledge, jumping, etc) that shouldn't be interrupted.

IsStuck.desc: Return true if bot is stuck. If the locomotor cannot make progress, it becomes stuck and can only leave this stuck state by successfully movingand becoming un-stuck.

Jump.desc: Initiate a simple undirected jump in the air.

JumpAcrossGap.desc: Initiate a jump across an empty volume of space to far side.

OnLandOnGround.desc: Manually run the OnLandOnGround callback. Typically invoked when bot lands on the ground after being in the air.

OnLeaveGround.desc: Manually run the OnLeaveGround callback. Typically invoked when bot leaves ground for any reason.

Run.desc: Set desired movement speed to running.

SetDesiredSpeed.desc: Set desired speed for locomotor movement.

SetSpeedLimit.desc: Set maximum speed bot can reach, regardless of desired speed.

Stop.desc: Set desired movement speed to stopped.

Walk.desc: Set desired movement speed to walking

capture.desc: Returns an array of tables containing two indexes ("begin" and "end") of the first match of the regular expression in the string str. An array entry is created for each captured sub expressions. If no match occurs returns null. The search starts from the index start of the string, if start is omitted the search starts from the beginning of the string.

match.desc: Returns a true if the regular expression matches the string str, otherwise returns false.

search.desc: Returns a table containing two indexes ("begin" and "end") of the first match of the regular expression in the string `str`, otherwise if no match occurs returns null. The search starts from the index start of the string, if start is omitted the search starts from the beginning of the string.

Cross.desc: The vector product of two vectors. Returns a vector orthogonal to the input vectors.

Dot.desc: The scalar product of two vectors.

LengthSqr.desc: The magnitude of the vector squared.

Length2D.desc: Returns the magnitude of the vector on the x-y plane.

Length2DSqr.desc: Returns the square of the magnitude of the vector on the x-y plane.

Norm.desc: Normalizes the vector/quaternion in place and returns it's length.

ToKVString.desc: Returns a string without separations commas.

Forward.desc: Returns the Forward Vector of the angles.

Pitch.desc: Returns the pitch angle in degrees.

Roll.desc: Returns the roll angle in degrees.

ToQuat.desc: Returns a quaternion representaion of the orientation.

Up.desc: Returns the Up Vector of the angles.

Yaw.desc: Returns the yaw angle in degrees.

Invert.desc: Returns a quaternion with the complimentary rotation.

SetPitchYawRoll.detail: Quaternion.SetPitchYawRoll(pitch: float, yaw: float, roll: float) -> null
SetPitchYawRoll.desc: Recomputes the quaternion from the supplied Euler angles.

ToQAngle.desc: Returns the angles resulting from the rotation.

find.detail: string.find(substring: string, start_index: int = 0) -> int | null
find.desc: Looks for the sub-string passed as its first parameter, starting at either the beginning of the string or at a specific character index if one is provided as a second parameter. If the sub-string is found, returns the index at which it first occurs, otherwise returns null.

slice.detail: string | array.slice(start_index: int, end_index: int = null) -> null
slice.desc: Returns a section of the string/array as new string/array. Copies from start to the end (not included). If start is negative the index is calculated as length + start, if end is negative the index is calculated as length + end. If end is omitted end is equal to the string/array length.

tolower.desc: Returns a new string with all upper-case characters converted to lower-case.

toupper.desc: Returns a new string with all lower-case characters converted to upper-case.

append.desc: Adds an item to the end of an array.

apply.desc: Applies a function to all of an array's items.

clear.desc: Removes all of the items from an array/table.

filter.desc: Applies a filter function to an array's items, storing the results in a new array.

insert.desc: Inserts an item into an array at the specified index.

map.desc: Applies a function an array's items, adding the results to a new array.

pop.desc: Returns and removes the value at the end of the array.

push.desc: Adds an item to the end of an array.

reduce.detail: array.reduce(func: function, initializer: any = null) -> any
reduce.desc: This method applies the supplied function to all of the items in the target array, starting with the first two. The function returns a single value which is then combined with the next (third) item in the array  and so on until all of the items have been combined into a single value which the method returns.

remove.desc: Returns and removes an array item at a specified index.

resize.detail: array.resize(new_size: int, fill: any = null) -> null
resize.desc: Increases or decreases the size of an array.

reverse.desc: Reverses the order of the elements in an array.

sort.desc: This method sorts the items within the target array into either a lowest-to-highest order or according to the results of an optional comparison function which may be passed to the method as a parameter. If the items are arrays, blobs, functions, objects and/or tables, they will be sorted by reference not value. The optional comparison function should take two parameters: two values which will be compared in some way. It should return the value -1 if the first value should be placed before the second, or 1 if it should follow the second value. Return 0 if the two values are equivalent.

top.desc: Returns the value at the end of an array.

rawdelete.desc: This method deletes the target slot without employing delegation. If the table lacks the target slot, the methods returns null, otherwise it returns the value associated with that slot.

rawget.desc: Retrieves the value of the specified key without employing delegation.

rawin.desc: Checks for the presence of the specified key in the table/class/handle without employing delegation.

rawset.detail: table | class | handle.rawset(key: any, value: any) -> any
rawset.desc: Sets the value of the specified key without employing delegation.

setdelegate.desc: This method assigns the passed table as the targets new custom delegate. The method always returns the target.To remove a delegate, either assign the target with a new delegate, or pass null.

keys.desc: Returns an array containing all the keys of the table slots.

values.desc: Returns an array containing all the values of the table slots.

acall.desc: Calls the target function and passes array values into its parameters.

bindenv.desc: Clones the target function and binds it to a specified context object.

call.desc: Calls the function with a non-default context object.

pcall.desc: Calls the function with a non-default context object, bypassing Squirrel error callbacks.

pacall.desc: Calls the function with an array of parameters, bypassing Squirrel error callbacks.

setroot.desc: Sets the root table of a closure

getroot.desc: Returns the root table of the closure

getinfos.desc: Returns a table containing informations about the function, like parameters, name and source name.

instance.desc: Returns a new instance of the class. this function does not invoke the instance constructor. The constructor must be explicitly called (eg. class_inst.constructor(class_inst) ).

getattributes.desc: Returns the attributes of the specified member. if the parameter member is null the function returns the class level attributes.

setattributes.desc: Sets the attribute of the specified member and returns the previous attribute value. if the parameter member is null the function sets the class level attributes.

newmember.detail: class.newmember(key: any, value: any, attrs: table = null, static: bool = false) -> null
newmember.desc: Sets/adds the slot `key` with the value `val` and attributes `attrs` and if present invokes the _newmember metamethod. If `static` is true the slot will be added as static. If the slot does not exists - it will be created.

rawnewmember.detail: class.rawnewmember(key: any, value: any, attrs: table = null, static: bool = false) -> null
rawnewmember.desc: Sets/adds the slot `key` with the value `val` and attributes `attrs`. If `static` is true the slot will be added as static. If the slot does not exists - it will be created.

getclass.desc: Returns the class that created the instance.

weakref.desc: Returns a weak reference to the object.

tofloat.desc: Returns float value represented by the integer/bool/float/string. For string it must only contain numeric characters and/or plus and minus symbols. An exception is thrown otherwise.

tointeger.detail: int | bool | float | string.tointeger(base: int = 10) -> int
tointeger.desc: Returns integer value represented by the integer/bool/float/string. For string it must only contain numeric characters. An exception is thrown otherwise. Hexadecimal notation is supported (i.e. 0xFF). If a hexadecimal string contains more than 10 characters, including the 0x, returns -1.

tochar.desc: Returns a string containing a single character represented by the integer/integer part of the float.

tostring.detail: int | bool | float | string | handle.tostring() -> string
tostring.desc: Returns a string representation of the corresponding data type. For handles/tables the default return behaviour can be redefined by using _tostring metamethod in the handle's class / table's delegate.

ref.desc: Returns the object that the weak reference is pointing at; null if the object that was point at was destroyed.

__KeyValueFromFloat.desc:
`( KeyValueFromFloat)`.

Behaves the same as `KeyValueFromFloat`, use that instead.

__KeyValueFromInt.desc:
`( KeyValueFromInt)`.

Behaves the same as `KeyValueFromInt`, use that instead.

__KeyValueFromString.desc:
`( KeyValueFromString)`.

Behaves the same as `KeyValueFromString`, use that instead.

__KeyValueFromVector.desc:
`( KeyValueFromVector)`.

Behaves the same as `KeyValueFromVector`, use that instead.

GetAngles.desc:
`( GetAbsAngles)`.

Get the entity's pitch, yaw, and roll as a **Vector**.

GetLeftVector.desc:
`( GetRightVector)`.

Get the *right* vector of the entity. This is purely for compatibility.

SetAngles.detail: CBaseEntity.SetAngles(pitch: float, yaw: float, roll: float) -> null

AddThinkToEnt.desc: Sets a function in the entity's script to rerun by itself constantly. Pass null as the function name to remove a think function.

Assert.desc: Test value and if not true, throws exception, optionally with message.

ClearGameEventCallbacks.desc: Empties the tables of game event callback functions.

CreateProp.detail: CreateProp(classname: string, origin: Vector, model_name: string, activity: int) -> handle

CreateSceneEntity.desc: Create a scene entity to play the specified scene.

developer.desc: The current level of the `developer` console variable.

DispatchParticleEffect.detail: DispatchParticleEffect(name: string, origin: Vector, direction: Vector) -> null
DispatchParticleEffect.desc: Dispatches a one-off particle system. To pass angles into this, use the `.Forward()` method on a QAngle.

Document.detail: Document(symbol_or_table: unknown, item_if_symbol: unknown = null, description_if_symbol: string = null) -> null

DoEntFire.detail: DoEntFire(target: string, action: string, value: string, delay: float, activator: handle, caller: handle) -> null
DoEntFire.desc: Generate an entity I/O event. The `caller` and `activator` argument takes a `CBaseEntity` script handle, and entities assigned can receive inputs with `target` set to *!self*, or *!activator* / *!caller*. Negative delays are clamped to 0.

DoIncludeScript.detail: DoIncludeScript(file: string, scope: table | handle) -> bool
DoIncludeScript.desc: Execute a script and put all its content for the argument passed to the `scope` parameter. The file must have the `.nut` extension.

IncludeScript.detail: IncludeScript(file: string, scope: table = null) -> bool

EmitAmbientSoundOn.detail: EmitAmbientSoundOn(sound_name: string, volume: float, soundlevel: int, pitch: int, entity: handle) -> null
EmitAmbientSoundOn.desc: Play named sound on an entity using configurations similar to [this page](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/ambient_generic]]. Soundlevel is in decibels, see [Soundscripts#SoundLevel](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Soundscripts#SoundLevel) for real world equivalents.

StopAmbientSoundOn.desc: Stop named sound on an entity using configurations similar to [ambient_generic](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/ambient_generic).

EmitSoundOn.desc: Play named sound on given entity. The sound must be precached first for it to play (using `PrecacheSound` or `PrecacheScriptSound`).

StopSoundOn.desc: Stop named sound on an entity.

EmitSoundOnClient.desc: Play named sound only on the client for the specified player. The sound must be precached first for it to play (`PrecacheScriptSound`).

EntFire.detail: EntFire(target: string, action: string, value: string = "", delay: float = 0.0, activator: handle = null) -> null
EntFire.desc: Wrapper for DoEntFire() that sets `activator` to null, but has no `caller` param. Negative delays are clamped to 0.

EntFireByHandle.detail: EntFireByHandle(entity: handle, action: string, value: string, delay: float, activator: handle, caller: handle) -> null
EntFireByHandle.desc: Generate an entity I/O event. First parameter is an entity instance. Negative delays are clamped to 0.

EntIndexToHScript.desc: Turn an entity index integer to an HScript representing that entity's script instance.

FileToString.desc: Reads a string from file located in the game's *scriptdata* folder. Returns the string from the file, null if no file or file is greater than 16384 bytes.

FireGameEvent.desc: Fire a game event to a listening callback function in script. Parameters are passed in a shared table.

FireScriptHook.desc: Fire a script hook to a listening callback function in script. Parameters are passed in a shared table.

FrameTime.desc: Get the time spent on the server in the last frame. Usually this will be 0.015 (the default tickrate).

GetFrameCount.desc: Returns the engines current frame count. The counter does not reset between map changes. This is NOT the tick count.

GetFriction.desc: Returns the Friction on a player entity, meaningless if not a player.

GetListenServerHost.desc: Get the local player on a listen server. Returns null on dedicated servers.

GetMapName.desc: Get the name of the map without extension, e.g. `ctf_2fort`. For workshop maps, this will be in the format `workshop/[name].ugc[id]`.

GetModelIndex.desc: Returns the index of the named model.

GetPlayerFromUserID.desc: Given a user id, return the entity, or null.

GetSoundDuration.detail: GetSoundDuration(sound_name: string, actor_model_name: string = null) -> float
GetSoundDuration.desc: Returns float duration of the sound. Actor model name is optional and can be left null.

IsDedicatedServer.desc: Returns true if this server is a dedicated server.

IsPlayerABot.desc: Is this player/entity a puppet or AI bot. To check if the player is a AI bot (`CTFBot`) specifically, use `IsBotOfType` instead.

LocalTime.desc: Fills out a table with the local time (second, minute, hour, day, month, year, dayofweek, dayofyear, daylightsavings). This mirrors the `tm` structure in C++, see the [https://cplusplus.com/reference/ctime/tm/ reference page] for more information.

MaxClients.desc: Get the current number of max clients set by the maxplayers command.

PickupObject.desc: Object from world is put into the "Held" slot of the player. Warning: it will smoothly interpolate from where it is to the players hand - which is a bit goofy if it is on other side of level.

PlayerInstanceFromIndex.desc: Get a script handle of a player using the player index.

TraceLine.detail: TraceLine(start: Vector, end: Vector, ignore: handle) -> float
TraceLine.desc: Trace a ray. Return fraction along line that hits world or models. Optionally, ignore the specified entity.

TraceLinePlayersIncluded.detail: TraceLinePlayersIncluded(start: Vector, end: Vector, ignore: handle) -> float
TraceLinePlayersIncluded.desc: Different version of `TraceLine` that also hits players and NPCs.

TraceLineEx.desc:
Extended version of `TraceLine`. See the [main page](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/TraceLineEx) for more details.

---
Input variables of the `params` table. The only required information to make the trace is providing the start and end point. The rest are optional:

```squirrelDoc
start: Vector
```
Point where to start the trace, in world coordinates.
```squirrelDoc
end: Vector
```
Point where to end the trace, in world coordinates. If the end is the same as the start, this will function as a point check, i.e. is the point inside any geometry.
```squirrelDoc
mask: int
```
Optional contents bitmask to include or exclude common groups of geometry, such as fences, NPCs, playerclips, etc. Default mask is `MASK_VISIBLE_AND_NPCS`. See constants page for a list of [contents](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FContents) and [common mask](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#MASK) types. By default this will trace against the bounding box of models only. Add `CONTENTS_HITBOX` to the mask to instead perform precise hitbox tests.
```squirrelDoc
ignore: handle
```
Optional entity to ignore when tracing. [worldspawn](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/worldspawn) cannot be ignored.

---
Output variables of the `params` table:
```squirrelDoc
pos: Vector
```
Point in world coordinates where the trace ended. Equal to end position if nothing was hit.
```squirrelDoc
fraction: float
```
 Fraction from the start to end where the trace ended. E.g. 0.0 is start, 1.0 is end.
```squirrelDoc
hit: bool
```
 Whether the trace hit something.
```squirrelDoc
enthit: handle
```
 If hit, the entity that was hit. This is not written to the table if hit was false.
```squirrelDoc
startsolid: bool
```
 Whether the trace started inside geometry. Only written if true.
```squirrelDoc
allsolid: bool
```
 If true, plane information is unavailable (started and ended inside geometry or didn't hit anything). Only written if true.
```squirrelDoc
startpos: Vector
```
 Starting position of the trace in world coordinates. Probably the same as start.
```squirrelDoc
endpos: Vector
```
 Ending position of the trace in world coordinates. Same as end if it didn't hit anything, otherwise this is the hit point.
```squirrelDoc
plane_normal: Vector
```
 If hit, the normal (unit) vector of the surface.
```squirrelDoc
plane_dist: float
```
 If hit, distance of surface plane from origin. Forms a plane equation with plane_normal.
```squirrelDoc
surface_name: string
```
 If hit, name of the surface's texture that was hit. Not available for displacements or models.
```squirrelDoc
surface_flags: int
```
If hit, bitmask of the surface flags. See [FSurf](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Team_Fortress_2/Scripting/Script_Functions/Constants#FSurf) constants.
```squirrelDoc
surface_props: int
```
If hit, the [surfaceprop](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/surfaceprop) of the surface. Note that this is an index rather than a string.

TraceHull.desc:

assert.desc: Throws an assertion error if the given expression evaluates to `false` (i.e. the values <tt>0, 0.0, null</tt> and <tt>false</tt>).

castf2i.desc: Interprets the float's bytes as if it were a 32-bit integer representation.

casti2f.desc: Interprets the integer's bytes as if it were a floating-point encoding.

collectgarbage.desc: Runs the garbage collector and returns the number of reference cycles found(and deleted) This function only works on garbage collector builds.

compilestring.detail: compilestring(string: string, buffer_name: string = null) -> any
compilestring.desc: Compiles a string containing a shared script into a function and returns it.

enabledebuginfo.desc: Enable/disable the debug line information generation at compile time. enable != null enables . enable == null disables.

error.desc: Prints x in the standard error output .

getconsttable.desc: Returns the const table of the VM.

getroottable.desc: Returns the root table of the VM.

getstackinfos.desc: Returns the stack frame informations at the given stack level (0 is the current function 1 is the caller and so on). If the stack level doesn't exist the function returns null.

newthread.desc: Creates a new cooperative thread object(coroutine) and returns it .

print.desc: Prints the given parameter but with no newline unlike `printl()`.

resurrectunreachable.desc: Runs the garbage collector and returns an array containing all unreachable object found. If no unreachable object is found, null is returned instead. This function is meant to help debugging reference cycles. This function only works on garbage collector builds.

setconsttable.desc: Sets the const table of the VM which also returns the previous const table.

setroottable.desc: Sets the root table of the VM which also returns the previous root table.

suspend.desc: Suspends the coroutine that called this function.

swap2.desc: Swaps bytes 1 and 2 of the integer.

swap4.desc: Reverse byte order of the four bytes.

swapfloat.desc: Reverse byte order of the four bytes.

type.desc: Returns var._typeof(), i.e. the type of the given parameter as a string

atan2.desc: Returns the angle between the ray from the point (0, 0) through (x, y) and the positive x-axis, confined to (PI, PI], See also [atan2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atan2). Note the order of the parameters x and y!]

ceil.desc: Returns the smallest integer that is  x.

floor.desc: Returns the largest integer that is  x.

rand.desc: Returns a random integer with `0  rand()  RAND_MAX`.

sqrt.desc: Returns the square root of x.

srand.desc: Sets the starting point for generating a series of pseudorandom integers.

endswith.desc: Returns true if the end of the string matches the comparison string.

escape.desc: Returns a string with backslashes before characters that need to be escaped: ` a b t n v f r \   0 xNN`.

format.desc: Returns a [formatted string](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Printf). Same rules as the standard C functions (except * is not supported).

lstrip.desc: Removes whitespace at the beginning of the given string.

rstrip.desc: Removes whitespace at the end of the given string.

split.detail: split(str: string, separator: string, skip_empty: bool = null) -> array
split.desc: Returns an array of strings split at each point where a separator character occurs in str. The separator is not returned as part of any array element. the parameter separators is a string that specifies the characters as to be used for the splitting. If skipempty is true, empty strings are not added to array.

startswith.desc: Returns true if the beginning of the string matches the comparison string.

strip.desc: Removes whitespace at the beginning and end of the given string

When map entities are respawned, this effectively runs after all scripts, players etc have been loaded. This could be used to have an entity register itself with a master script, or adjusting the entity parameters in a programmatic way.

IsConVarOnAllowList.desc: Checks if the convar is allowed to be used and is in cfg/vscript_convar_allowlist.txt. Please be nice with this and use it for *compatibility* if you need check support and NOT to force server owners to allow hostname to be set... or else this will simply lie and return true in future. ;-) You have been warned!

SetValue.desc: Sets the value of the convar. The convar must be in cfg/vscript_convar_allowlist.txt to be set. Convars marked as cheat-only can be set even if *sv_cheats* is off. Convars marked as dev-only (i.e. not visible in console) can also be set. Supported types are bool, int, float, string. The original value of the convar is saved and is reset on map change, in other words convar changes will not persist across maps.
